INSERT INTO `DA_Pages` VALUES(212, 'How I Can Help', '\r\n&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; color: navy;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: navy; font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight: bold; font-family: arial;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;How Can I Help?&lt;/h2&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Glad you asked. First of all, we need to tell you how much we appreciate all of you who show up for this event every year. We love having the opportunity to see your smiling faces and to count on your participation.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;As the GGO has grown there seems to be a few more things to do each year to make the event successful. We feel fortunate to have a large group of family and friends with many talents who pitch in for this event, but the day of the event is always pretty busy. If you have an interest in making yourself available to assist in the "Day of the Event" activities. Just get in touch with us, the contact information is listed at the bottom of this page.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;In addition to the volunteer help we always need assistance in gathering merchandise and fundraising for the event. Below are some suggestions that help in that area. If you or someone you know has an interest in assisting in any of the areas specified below, please let us know. We spend considerable time scrambling the days just before the tournament to gather up and organize the merchandise and prizes that we use for the event. Any help in getting more merchandise or getting it sooner would be greatly appreciated and would make the days just before the tournament a little less hectic. Here are some ideas.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;1. GIFTS, PRIZES AND MERCHANDISE. These items are particularly for the raffle, silent auction and hole events. Many of you have already helped with this in past events. It''s great when almost everyone who attends the event leaves with some kind of prize. For the last 3 events, EVERYTHING we gave away for prizes, raffle and Hole events were donated or covered by hole sponsorships. Gift certificates, golf merchandise, coolers, and anything you think would make a good prize, makes it a great day.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If you have a talent for making crafts or can provide a service for a gift, we welcome those as well. Some examples from this past year: A gift certificate for services from Kolbow Decorating, homemade table cloth and napkins, A week at a resort donated by the owners, Rounds of golf for two at local golf clubs..&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;2. HOLE SPONSORSHIPS. The cost to Sponsor a hole is 150.00. Our sponsorships help us purchase prizes for winners of hole events and the tournament. The more we get the more we can give out. A sign is made up with your company name and placed on one of the prize holes.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;3. QUILTS. The money raised from the Quilt raffle has become a substantial part of our fund raiser. We will always have room for more quilts.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;4. SILENT AUCTION. We have raised quite a bit of money in years past on the silent auction. All items are donated to the Good Guy and can be a variety of things. A few things that have been donated in the past are: autographed football, Massage certificate, weekend getaway, golf clubs, fishing rods, prints, garden benches, filled theme baskets, and more.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;5. IDEAS AND SUGGESTIONS. Many of you have been involved in similar fund raisers and may have some suggestions on how we could improve this event, make it more fun, or raise more money. We are open to anything you have to say. Send suggestions to krystallawson@yahoo.com or give us a call.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If you would like to speak to someone. Call Krystal Lawson at 651-464-3364, or Kelly Becker at 651-464-6640. You can also contact Krystal via email at krystallawson@yahoo.com, or use the Good Guy Open email address: goodguyopen@goodguyopen.com&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;THANKS FOR ALL YOUR SUPPORT!&lt;/p&gt;', '2013-07-10 09:23:15', 38, 78, '\0', 0, '\0', 0, 0, '');
